<p class="mt-3">
    Toasts are shown imperatively through <code>IToastService.Show&lt;TComponent&gt;</code>, which
    renders any component as the toast body and auto-dismisses it after
    <code>ToastOptions.Duration</code> (5 seconds by default). A body declares itself as a toast
    by inheriting <code>HBToast</code> - that base exposes <code>DismissAsync()</code> directly, so
    a close button can dismiss the toast early with no cascading parameter or wiring required.
    Showing a toast never blocks the caller - unlike a modal, there's no result to await.
</p>

